channel.title: Engine Load? DSPK
channel.description: Why engine load going up so high with no one playing? :[code=java][12/1/11 4:02 PM]: Average Cycle Time: 3ms [12/1/11 4:02 PM]: Players online: 0, engine load: 0.5% [12/1/11 4:08 PM]: Average Cycle Time: 2ms [12/1/11 4:08 PM]: Players online: 0, engine load: 0.33% [12/1/11 4:14 PM]: Average Cycle Time: 2ms[/code] I made the engine time go faster, but it still slows down, some of the problem is my hiscores, vote4cash, and auto donation. I have them save in the process, so it auto-updates, but even then it's kinda a large engine load. Anyone know where the memory leaks are? I found some, and fixed some of it. Like: byte[], char[], int[] and others. I'm not sure if I fixed them all though, I used virtualvm to find them. So, anyone know what I should do?
